[Australia was one of the 1st countries in the Western Pacific to be declared measles-free, underlining the effectiveness of the nation's comprehensive vaccination program. This report highlights the importance of being vaccinated with MMR vaccine even in a country declared free of measles because of the risk of travel-related infection.

